  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Soak your <strong>skewers</strong> in <strong>cold water</strong> (this prevents them from burning whilst cooking)</p><p>Chop the<strong> potatoes</strong> (skins on) into rough bite-sized pieces</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-1-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-1-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-1-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-1-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-1-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Top and tail the <strong>courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p><p>Chop the<strong> trimmed courgette<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> in half lengthways, then into half moons</p><p>Chop the<strong> tofu</strong> into 18 <span class=\"text-danger\">[36]</span> cubes</p><p>Peel and roughly chop the <strong>red onions</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-2-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-2-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-2-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-2-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-2-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the<strong> tofu cubes</strong>, <strong>chopped courgette</strong>, <strong>red onion wedges </strong>and <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> to a large bowl</p><p>Drizzle with <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and give everything a gentle mix up</p><p>Thread the<strong> chopped veg</strong> and<strong> tofu cubes</strong> onto the <strong>soaked skewers</strong>, alternating as you go – these are your <strong>tofu kebabs</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-3-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-3-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-3-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes </strong>to a baking tray with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>and a pinch of<strong> salt</strong></p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 20-25 min or until golden and crispy</p><p>Add the <strong>tofu kebabs</strong> to a separate lightly oiled baking tray and put the tray in the oven for an initial 15-20 min, or until everything has softened and beginning to turn golden</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> to a pot with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and 50ml<span class=\"text-danger\"> [100ml] </span><strong>cold water</strong></p><p>Add the pot to a medium-high heat and bring to the boil</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to medium and cook for 3-5 min or until reduced – this is your <strong>balsamic glaze</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/2201.-step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
